WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.667
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:02.750 --> 00:04.083
CALIFORNIA
CHILDREN'S SERVICES

00:04.166 --> 00:05.417
WILL NOT ALLOW ME TO PERFORM
THE SURGERY

00:05.500 --> 00:07.166
UNTIL YOU'RE OFFICIALLY
EMANCIPATED.

00:07.250 --> 00:08.709
WHAT IF
I CAN MAKE THAT HAPPEN?

00:08.792 --> 00:10.709
ALEXA, MEET ME OUTSIDE
THE HOSPITAL IN AN HOUR.

00:10.792 --> 00:12.583
[ PAGER BEEPS ]
Jordi: WHAT IS THAT?
IT'S MY UNOS PAGER.

00:12.667 --> 00:14.250
NEW LIVER FLYING IN,
PEOPLE!

00:14.333 --> 00:15.709
I'M ASHLEY,
HUNTER'S SISTER.

00:15.792 --> 00:17.125
Dr. McAndrew:
IF I HURT YOUR FEELINGS

00:17.208 --> 00:18.500
OR I MISLED YOU IN ANY WAY,
I APOLOGIZE,

00:18.583 --> 00:20.417
BUT EITHER GET OVER IT
OR GET OUT.

00:20.500 --> 00:21.750
Leo: APPARENTLY,
I NEED MORE TIME.

00:21.834 --> 00:23.458
Man: THE POWERS THAT BE
ARE THINKING

00:23.542 --> 00:25.125
ONE MORE WEEK,
POSSIBLY TWO.

00:25.208 --> 00:26.709
HONEY --
I WILL <i>NEVER</i>
UNDERSTAND YOU, MOM!

00:26.792 --> 00:27.750
I HATE YOU!

00:27.834 --> 00:29.875
Jon: EMMA, OPEN THIS DOOR!

00:29.959 --> 00:32.375
Kara: I WANT YOU TO FORGET
ABOUT ALL OF US. ESPECIALLY HER.

00:32.458 --> 00:34.208
I'M SORRY, KARA. I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GONNA BE POSSIBLE.

00:34.291 --> 00:35.542
WHY NOT?

00:35.625 --> 00:38.625
'CAUSE HOW COULD
ANYBODY EVER FORGET YOU?

00:41.917 --> 00:46.041
Charlie:
<i>MY POP-POP ONCE TOLD ME THAT</i>
<i>GUILT IS A USELESS EMOTION.</i>

00:46.125 --> 00:47.583
<i>MIND YOU, HE TOLD ME THIS</i>

00:47.667 --> 00:49.834
<i>FROM BEHIND THE GLASS</i>
<i>AT SAN QUENTIN.</i>

00:49.917 --> 00:53.250
<i>BUT STILL,</i>
<i>I THINK HE WAS ONTO SOMETHING.</i>

00:53.333 --> 00:54.417
<i>GUILT CRIPPLES YOU,</i>

00:54.500 --> 00:56.250
<i>MAKES YOU SECOND-GUESS</i>

00:56.333 --> 00:58.750
<i>ALL THE DECISIONS YOU BELIEVED</i>
<i>WERE GOOD AT THE TIME.</i>

00:58.834 --> 01:01.750
<i>POP-POP THOUGHT THAT TAX FRAUD</i>
<i>WAS A FINE OPTION,</i>

01:01.834 --> 01:03.750
<i>JUST LIKE THESE TWO WERE SURE</i>

01:03.834 --> 01:05.625
<i>SLEEPING TOGETHER</i>
<i>WOULD BE NO BIG DEAL.</i>

01:05.709 --> 01:07.250
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:07.333 --> 01:10.125
<i>OF COURSE, YOU CAN'T</i>
<i>KEEP GUILT IN FOREVER.</i>

01:10.208 --> 01:13.041
<i>EVENTUALLY YOU HAVE TO CONFRONT</i>
<i>THE THINGS YOU'VE DONE,</i>

01:13.125 --> 01:16.333
<i>EVEN IF THAT DISCUSSION</i>
<i>LEAVES SOMETHING TO BE DESIRED.</i>

01:18.375 --> 01:19.417
SO,
WE DON'T HAVE TO EVER --

01:19.500 --> 01:21.917
WASN'T PLANNING ON IT.

01:22.000 --> 01:23.083
THAT'S GOOD,
'CAUSE IT --

01:23.166 --> 01:24.542
IT DIDN'T HAPPEN.

01:24.625 --> 01:26.458
RIGHT. SO --
LEO, IT'S LATE.

01:26.542 --> 01:28.542
AND AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,

01:28.625 --> 01:30.041
ABOUT THIS AGAIN.TALK

01:30.125 --> 01:31.834
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:31.917 --> 01:34.208
IT'S ABOUT DAMN TIME.

01:34.291 --> 01:35.959
LOOK, I LEFT SOMETHING
ON YOUR BED.

01:36.041 --> 01:37.333
HEY, WHAT DID YOU LEAVE
ON HER BED?

01:37.417 --> 01:39.041
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I LEFT ON HER BED

01:39.125 --> 01:40.709
WHEN YOU TELL ME WHERE THE HELL
Y'ALL BEEN ALL NIGHT, MAN.

01:40.792 --> 01:42.250
SORRY.
I LOST TRACK OF TIME.

01:42.333 --> 01:44.166
SO YOU DON'T HAVE
A PHONE?
IT DIED.

01:44.250 --> 01:45.959
AND WE WENT TO THIS COFFEE SHOP
TO TRY AND CHARGE IT,

01:46.041 --> 01:47.792
AND THE GUYS WERE LIKE,
"NO, YOU CAN'T USE MY OUTLET.

01:47.875 --> 01:49.000
I'M WRITING A SCREENPLAY."

01:49.083 --> 01:51.375
SO WE JUST LEFT.

01:51.458 --> 01:52.917
YOU BANGED!

01:53.000 --> 01:55.250
YO, I KNEW IT!
YOU HAD THAT LOOK ON YOUR FACE.

01:55.333 --> 01:56.709
KARA'S HAIR'S
ALL MESSED UP.

01:56.792 --> 01:58.333
AND, FRANKLY,
I CAN SMELL IT ON YOU, MAN.

01:58.417 --> 01:59.709
I'VE DEVELOPED A NOSE.

01:59.792 --> 02:01.500
I WOULD NOT SHARE THAT
WITH PEOPLE.

02:01.583 --> 02:03.291
ALL RIGHT, I NEED THE DETAILS.
WAS YOUR LEG ON OR OFF?

02:03.375 --> 02:05.792
UH, IT STARTED ON
AND IT CAME OFF.
WHAT?

02:05.875 --> 02:07.542
THAT'S ALL YOU'RE GETTING.
I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

02:07.625 --> 02:09.834
DUDE, I DO NOT WANT YOU
TO FEEL GUILTY ABOUT THIS.

02:09.917 --> 02:11.417
GUILT IS AN UNHEALTHY EMOTION,
MAN.

02:11.500 --> 02:13.166
IT'S ANTITHETICAL
IN OUR WORLD'S EXISTENCE.

02:13.250 --> 02:14.917
DO YOU THINK CHEETAHS REGRET
KILLING GAZELLES?

02:15.000 --> 02:16.667
NO, BECAUSE THEY KNOW
THAT IF THEY DIDN'T,

02:16.750 --> 02:18.417
WE'D HAVE AN OVERFLOW OF HOOFED
CREATURES ON OUR PLANET,

02:18.500 --> 02:19.917
AND THEN
WHERE WOULD WE BE?

02:20.000 --> 02:22.083
I DO NOT FEEL GUILTY.
NOT EVEN A LITTLE BIT?

02:22.166 --> 02:24.542
NO! WHY SHOULD I?
EMMA BROKE UP WITH <i>ME.</i>

02:24.625 --> 02:26.000
SHE DIDN'T RETURN
ANY OF MY CALLS,

02:26.083 --> 02:27.583
AND IT'S VERY CLEAR
SHE WANTS TO MOVE ON.

02:27.667 --> 02:29.667
LEO, I'VE BEEN LOOKING
EVERYWHERE FOR YOU.

02:29.750 --> 02:30.750
WHY?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:30.834 --> 02:32.333
IT'S EMMA.

02:32.417 --> 02:34.166
HER DAD BROUGHT HER
INTO THE E.R. A FEW HOURS AGO.

02:34.250 --> 02:35.333
THE E.R.?
WHAT?

02:35.417 --> 02:37.917
COME ON.KING FOR YOU.

02:38.000 --> 02:39.875
<i>THAT'S ANOTHER THING</i>
<i>ABOUT GUILT.</i>

02:39.959 --> 02:42.333
<i>YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN</i>
<i>IT'LL SPRING YOU INTO ACTION</i>

02:42.417 --> 02:45.667
<i>EITHER FOR GOOD OR FOR BAD.</i>

02:45.750 --> 02:48.041
NICELY DONE.
MONEY FIRST.

02:48.125 --> 02:49.500
[ SIGHS ]

02:49.583 --> 02:52.291
$300. IT'S ALL HERE.

02:53.667 --> 02:54.959
BY THE WAY,
I HAVE A FRIEND

02:55.041 --> 02:56.583
WHO MIGHT WANT
TO GET IN ON THE ACTION.

02:56.667 --> 02:58.041
ALL RIGHT, THIS IS ONLY
A MEANS TO AN END FOR ME.

02:58.125 --> 02:59.542
I'M NOT ACTUALLY A DRUG DEALER,
ALEXA.

02:59.625 --> 03:02.959
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT
MY OTHER DRUG DEALER SAYS.

03:16.458 --> 03:17.875
DR. McANDREW.

03:17.959 --> 03:19.291
HEY.

03:19.375 --> 03:22.375
UM, HUNTER IS STABILIZED
AND IN RECOVERY.

03:22.458 --> 03:23.875
OH.
I THOUGHT
YOU'D WANT TO KNOW.

03:23.959 --> 03:26.041
THANK YOU. YEAH.
OKAY.

03:26.125 --> 03:27.083
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

03:27.166 --> 03:29.500
NO, UM, BRITTANY.

03:29.583 --> 03:32.625
I'M SORRY FOR SNAPPING
AT YOU BEFORE.

03:32.709 --> 03:33.625
THAT WAS...

03:33.709 --> 03:35.166
IT'S FINE.

03:35.250 --> 03:36.959
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S -- IT'S -- IT'S NOT FINE.

03:37.041 --> 03:39.959
THERE ARE, UH, DOZENS OF WAYS
I COULD HAVE TOLD YOU --

03:40.041 --> 03:42.000
TO GROW UP?

03:42.083 --> 03:44.917
[ SCOFFS ]
THERE IS ONLY ONE WAY.

03:45.000 --> 03:46.917
UM, SOMETIMES,
YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT,

03:47.000 --> 03:50.291
BUT SOMETIMES,
YOU HAVE TO.

03:50.375 --> 03:52.667
AND YOU WERE RIGHT,
SO THANK YOU.

03:52.750 --> 03:55.083
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THAT'S VERY MATURE OF YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:55.166 --> 03:57.709
WELL, THERE ARE SOME BENEFITS
TO WATCHING OWN.

03:57.792 --> 03:59.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:59.417 --> 04:00.583
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

04:00.667 --> 04:03.834
OH, AND, UM, FYI --

04:03.917 --> 04:07.083
YOU HAVE
A DROOL SITUATION.

04:07.166 --> 04:09.000
YEAH.

04:09.083 --> 04:10.417
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:17.834 --> 04:19.125
[ SCOFFS ]

04:19.208 --> 04:21.542
OH, MY GOD.
SERIOUSLY, HUNTER?

04:23.166 --> 04:26.041
CHARLIE. YOU AWAKE?

04:27.750 --> 04:29.834
WHAT IS THIS?
SOME SAPPY GOODBYE LETTER?

04:29.917 --> 04:31.792
SHOULD I EVEN OPEN THIS?

04:31.875 --> 04:33.542
I SHOULDN'T, RIGHT?

04:35.125 --> 04:36.875
BLINK ONCE FOR YES,
TWICE FOR NO.

04:39.875 --> 04:41.500
WAIT.
WAS THAT ONCE OR TWICE?

04:41.583 --> 04:43.166
<i>NEITHER.</i>

04:43.250 --> 04:44.834
<i>I'M MORSE-CODING GOD</i>
<i>TO MAKE YOU GO AWAY.</i>

04:44.917 --> 04:47.667
FINE.
I'LL OPEN IT.

04:47.750 --> 04:50.792
PROBABLY
SOME PRETENTIOUS POEM

04:50.875 --> 04:54.083
ABOUT CONSCIOUS UNCOUPLING
OR SOME WEIR--

04:56.917 --> 05:01.166
"PRE-STATED DISPENSATION"?

05:01.250 --> 05:03.583
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

05:07.000 --> 05:09.250
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW THIS HAPPENED.

05:09.333 --> 05:11.291
SHE MADE WEIGHT.
SHE WAS CLEARED TO GO HOME.

05:11.375 --> 05:13.166
THERE'S A TIPPING POINT
WITH ANOREXIA.

05:13.250 --> 05:14.750
NOW, I'M NOT SAYING
EMMA'S THERE YET,

05:14.834 --> 05:16.333
BUT WE MAY BE SEEING

05:16.417 --> 05:18.125
THE BEGINNING OF LONG-TERM
EFFECTS TO HER HEALTH,

05:18.208 --> 05:20.875
WHICH ARE IRREVERSIBLE.

05:25.875 --> 05:26.834
LEO.

05:26.917 --> 05:29.208
EMMA, WHAT HAPPENED?

05:29.291 --> 05:31.500
I FAINTED,
AND I HIT MY HEAD,

05:31.583 --> 05:33.709
AND NOW THE DOCTOR THINKS
I'VE DONE IRREVERSIBLE DAMAGE.

05:33.792 --> 05:35.291
Dr. Parker:
WELL, WE DON'T KNOW THAT YET.

05:35.375 --> 05:36.875
LIKE I SAID,
WE HAVE TO DO MORE TESTS.

05:36.959 --> 05:38.458
HELLO, LEO.

05:38.542 --> 05:40.500
MR. CHOTA, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO INTERRUPT.

05:40.583 --> 05:41.834
NO, I'M -- I'M GLAD
YOU'RE HERE.

05:41.917 --> 05:43.041
EMMA'S BEEN ASKING
FOR YOU.

05:43.125 --> 05:44.917
IN FACT, NOW THAT YOU ARE,

05:45.000 --> 05:47.208
I SHOULD GO CALL MY WIFE AND
LET HER KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.

05:47.291 --> 05:49.041
BE BACK IN A BIT.

05:49.125 --> 05:52.709
I'LL TALK TO YOU SOON.
MR. CHOTA.

05:55.250 --> 05:57.500
I'M SO EMBARRASSED
ABOUT EVERYTHING, LEO.

05:57.583 --> 05:58.709
PLEASE DON'T HATE ME.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.208
OF COURSE I DON'T HATE YOU.

06:00.291 --> 06:01.500
IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY.

06:01.583 --> 06:03.500
NO, IT'S NOT.

06:03.583 --> 06:05.333
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER LEFT
THE HOSPITAL

06:05.417 --> 06:07.875
OR SAID
ANYTHING THAT I SAID.

06:11.250 --> 06:14.542
WILL YOU STAY WITH ME?
PLEASE?

06:15.750 --> 06:17.166
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

06:22.834 --> 06:26.250
NURSE JACKSON, BEFORE YOU GO
HOME AND BINGE-WATCH "CASTLE,"

06:26.333 --> 06:27.250
I NEED YOU.

06:27.333 --> 06:28.667
KARA, MY SHIFT IS OVER.

06:28.750 --> 06:30.750
SO UNLESS YOUR EYEBALLS
ARE FALLING OUT,

06:30.834 --> 06:32.875
MAY I DIRECT YOU
TO THE NIGHT STAFF?

06:34.667 --> 06:37.667
PLEASE, I JUST NEED YOU
TO TELL ME WHAT THIS IS.

06:43.667 --> 06:45.583
WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

06:45.667 --> 06:48.917
HUNTER LEFT IT FOR ME
BEFORE HE WAS DISCHARGED.

06:49.000 --> 06:51.208
OH, HONEY.

06:51.291 --> 06:53.166
LOOK.

06:54.542 --> 06:57.917
HUNTER DIDN'T LEAVE.
HE GOT PAGED.

06:58.041 --> 06:59.458
HIS LIVER CAME IN
FROM SACRAMENTO.

06:59.542 --> 07:00.709
HE WENT
STRAIGHT INTO THE O.R.

07:00.792 --> 07:01.625
I NEED TO GO SEE HIM.
YOU CAN'T.

07:01.709 --> 07:03.000
HE'S IN THE ICU.

07:03.083 --> 07:04.875
NOW, THE NEXT 48 HOURS
ARE CRUCIAL.

07:04.959 --> 07:06.834
WE ARE MONITORING HIM
AROUND THE CLOCK.

07:06.917 --> 07:08.166
WHY?

07:08.250 --> 07:10.959
TO SEE IF HIS BODY
REJECTS THE ORGAN.

07:11.041 --> 07:14.125
WHICH IS WHY HE SIGNED
THIS DIRECT DONATION TO YOU.

07:14.208 --> 07:18.125
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

07:18.208 --> 07:21.542
KARA,
IF HUNTER DOESN'T MAKE IT,

07:21.625 --> 07:23.667
HE'S LEAVING YOU HIS HEART.

07:23.750 --> 07:25.750
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

07:31.792 --> 07:34.792
-- Captions by VITAC --

07:37.417 --> 07:41.500
<i>GUILT -- OTHERWISE KNOWN</i>
<i>AS NATURE'S CAFFEINE.</i>

07:41.583 --> 07:43.166
<i>I ONCE COULDN'T SLEEP</i>

07:43.250 --> 07:45.417
<i>BECAUSE I ACCIDENTALLY</i>
<i>STEPPED ON A LADY BUG.</i>

07:45.500 --> 07:47.959
<i>IMAGINE HOW KARA FEELS</i>
<i>KNOWING THAT SHE CHEATED</i>

07:48.041 --> 07:51.000
<i>ON THE GUY WHO LITERALLY</i>
<i>GAVE HER HIS HEART.</i>

07:51.083 --> 07:52.583
Dr. McAndrew:
OF COURSE I KNEW ABOUT IT.

07:52.667 --> 07:54.083
DR. KING MENTIONED IT

07:54.166 --> 07:55.875
SO THERE WAS A PLAN
TO PROCURE THE HEART

07:55.959 --> 07:57.583
IN THE EVENT THAT HUNTER
DOESN'T PULL THROUGH SURGERY.

07:57.667 --> 07:58.917
AND HE DID HIS HOMEWORK.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.000
HE FOUND OUT
THEY WERE A BLOOD MATCH.

08:00.083 --> 08:01.542
BUT KARA
DIDN'T KNOW.

08:01.625 --> 08:03.083
AND NOW THAT SHE DOES,
SHE'S FREAKING OUT.

08:03.166 --> 08:05.250
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME ABOUT THIS?

08:05.333 --> 08:06.917
I DIDN'T THINK
I NEEDED TO.

08:07.000 --> 08:08.583
WHAT'S --
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

08:08.667 --> 08:10.458
FOR STARTERS,
HE'S AN ORGAN DONOR,

08:10.542 --> 08:12.250
AND I HAVE
MUCH SICKER PATIENTS

08:12.333 --> 08:14.083
WHO ARE DEPENDING
ON TRANSPLANTS.

08:14.166 --> 08:15.542
KARA'S NOT EVEN
ON THE UNOS LIST.

08:15.625 --> 08:16.834
I KNOW.
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

08:16.917 --> 08:18.750
WHEN A PATIENT SIGNS
A LEGAL FORM,

08:18.834 --> 08:20.417
OUR HANDS ARE TIED,
END OF STORY.

08:20.500 --> 08:22.875
NOT IF THAT PATIENT
WASN'T IN HIS RIGHT MIND.

08:22.959 --> 08:24.000
WE BOTH KNOW
THAT SEVERE LIVER FAILURE

08:24.083 --> 08:25.709
CAN CAUSE DELUSIONAL THOUGHTS.

08:25.792 --> 08:28.500
OKAY, I'M NOT GONNA STAND HERE
AND SAY THAT KARA'S A SAINT.

08:28.583 --> 08:30.542
BUT SHE OBVIOUSLY
GOT THROUGH TO HUNTER,

08:30.625 --> 08:32.000
SO MAYBE HE'S MADE
A DIFFERENCE IN HER.

08:32.083 --> 08:33.291
MAYBE SHE'S CHANGED.

08:33.375 --> 08:35.542
SHE'S NOT QUALIFIED
FOR THE HEART.

08:35.625 --> 08:37.792
YOU DON'T GET TO MAKE
THE DECISION.
NO.

08:37.875 --> 08:40.792
BUT I DO GET TO APPEAL.
AND I WILL.

08:40.875 --> 08:42.875
FINE.

08:42.959 --> 08:44.458
THANK YOU.

08:44.542 --> 08:46.458
THANK YOU.

08:46.542 --> 08:48.458
GLAD TO SEE YOU TWO
BEING SO DIPLOMATIC.

08:48.542 --> 08:50.625
THAT'S NEW.

08:50.709 --> 08:52.625
WELL, WHEN THE GENEVA CONVENTION
RESUMES,

08:52.709 --> 08:54.166
TRY TO KEEP
IN PERSPECTIVE

08:54.250 --> 08:55.709
THAT HUNTER COLE
IS STILL CRITICAL

08:55.792 --> 08:57.333
BUT VERY MUCH ALIVE.

08:57.417 --> 09:00.375
FOR THE TIME BEING,
HIS HEART BELONGS TO HIM.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.917
MM.
I MEAN, I LIKE IT.

09:06.000 --> 09:07.917
THE CUT GOES
AGAINST YOUR FRAME,

09:08.000 --> 09:10.333
BUT THE PINSTRIPES,
THEY CREATE A STORY.

09:10.417 --> 09:13.333
PERSONALLY, I'D ROCK A FEDORA
WITH THIS ENSEMBLE.

09:13.417 --> 09:15.250
I'M NOT WEARING A HAT
WITH THIS, DASH.

09:15.333 --> 09:17.709
WHAT? A FEDORA'S MORE
THAN JUST A HAT, MAN.

09:17.792 --> 09:18.959
IT'S A STATEMENT.

09:19.041 --> 09:20.500
LET ME GO GET
SOME EXAMPLES.

09:20.583 --> 09:23.000
OH, ARE YOU INTO SOMETHING
LIKE A-A DEEP PLUM?

09:23.083 --> 09:24.375
NO.

09:24.458 --> 09:26.500
I COULD LEND YOU
A DIFFERENT-COLOR TIE.

09:26.583 --> 09:29.041
UH, THANKS,
BUT I THINK I'M GOOD.

09:29.125 --> 09:30.834
SHOULDN'T YOU BE DOWNSTAIRS
WITH EMMA?

09:30.917 --> 09:33.834
HER DOCTORS KICKED ME OUT.
THEY'RE RUNNING MORE TESTS.

09:33.917 --> 09:37.000
UH, DID YOU ALL GRADUATE
MED SCHOOL IN THE PAST 12 HOURS?

09:37.083 --> 09:38.875
THAT'S SARCASM

09:38.959 --> 09:40.834
FOR, "WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN THE DOCTORS' LOUNGE?"

09:40.917 --> 09:43.750
SORRY. THIS IS THE ONLY PLACE
WITH A FULL-LENGTH MIRROR.

09:43.834 --> 09:45.709
I'M GOING TO COURT
TODAY.

09:45.792 --> 09:47.959
TODAY?
OKAY, WELL, YOU STAY.

09:48.041 --> 09:49.667
YOU, DR. McANDREW
MOVED YOUR SCAN

09:49.750 --> 09:51.542
UP TO 3:00
THIS AFTERNOON.

09:51.625 --> 09:53.417
MIGHT PUT A BIT OF A CRIMP
IN MY SCHEDULE...

09:53.500 --> 09:55.208
IF I HAD A SCHEDULE.

09:55.291 --> 09:57.041
THAT'S SARCASM FOR,
"NO PROBLEM."

09:57.125 --> 09:58.375
GOOD.
NOW, GO TO YOUR ROOM.

09:58.458 --> 10:00.041
THERE'S A SURPRISE
WAITING FOR YOU.

10:00.125 --> 10:01.208
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

10:01.291 --> 10:03.500
HEY, GOOD LUCK TODAY,
MAN.

10:03.583 --> 10:05.583
HOW ARE YOU SEEING
THE JUDGE TODAY?

10:05.667 --> 10:07.875
MEGAN TOLD ME
YOUR FINAL EMANCIPATION HEARING

10:07.959 --> 10:09.291
WASN'T HAPPENING
FOR A FEW WEEKS.

10:09.375 --> 10:11.041
SHE GOT MY APPOINTMENT
MOVED UP.

10:11.125 --> 10:13.208
WELL, DID SHE CONTACT ANYONE
IN YOUR FAMILY TO LET THEM KNOW?

10:13.291 --> 10:16.333
SMOKE SIGNALS SHOULD REACH
MY MOM IN ABOUT A YEAR,

10:16.417 --> 10:17.959
DEPENDING ON WHERE SHE IS.

10:18.041 --> 10:20.083
MY ABUELA -- NO WORD.

10:20.166 --> 10:21.375
NO SURPRISE.

10:21.458 --> 10:22.625
I'M SORRY, JORDI.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.458
IT'S OKAY.
I'M USED TO IT.

10:27.875 --> 10:30.959
SURPRISE!
SURPRISE! [ LAUGHS ]

10:31.041 --> 10:33.792
MOM! DAD!
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING HERE?

10:33.875 --> 10:36.125
OH, YOU KNOW,
WE'RE JUST IN THE 'HOOD.

10:36.208 --> 10:37.959
YOUR MOM WANTED TO CHECK OUT
THE NEW EREWHON.

10:38.041 --> 10:39.709
WELL, I DID.
AND WE WILL.

10:39.792 --> 10:41.959
BUT FIRST...

10:42.041 --> 10:43.208
WE'RE HERE
TO BRING YOU HOME.

10:43.291 --> 10:44.875
BUT HOW?

10:44.959 --> 10:46.375
MY P.T. GUY SAID I COULDN'T
LEAVE FOR ANOTHER WEEK.

10:46.458 --> 10:48.542
HE TOLD US THE SAME THING,
SO WE MADE A FEW CALLS

10:48.625 --> 10:50.625
AND FOUND THIS GREAT
REHAB FACILITY RIGHT NEAR US.

10:50.709 --> 10:52.250
THEY HAVE
EVERYTHING YOU NEED.

10:52.333 --> 10:53.750
AND SINCE YOU'RE ALREADY
IN REMISSION,

10:53.834 --> 10:55.166
THERE DIDN'T SEEM
TO BE ANY GOOD REASON

10:55.250 --> 10:56.417
TO KEEP YOU HERE
FOR ANOTHER MINUTE.

10:56.500 --> 10:58.375
WHAT?
THIS IS HAPPENING NOW?

10:58.458 --> 10:59.792
MM-HMM.
YEAH.

10:59.875 --> 11:01.291
WELL, WE HAVE TO SIGN
THE DISCHARGE PAPERS,

11:01.375 --> 11:03.083
AND WE KNOW YOU HAVE
ANOTHER SCAN THIS AFTERNOON.

11:03.166 --> 11:05.125
WHICH WILL GIVE ME PLENTY
OF TIME TO HIT THE EREWHON,

11:05.208 --> 11:08.458
BECAUSE I AM MAKING YOU
THE ZITI TO END ALL ZITIS.

11:08.542 --> 11:10.166
YOU'LL BE BACK
IN YOUR OWN ROOM TONIGHT.

11:10.250 --> 11:12.000
HOW'S THAT SOUND, KID?

11:13.417 --> 11:17.041
UH, IT SOUNDS AMAZING.
THAT SOUNDS AMAZING.

11:17.125 --> 11:19.041
OH, BABY.
[ SMOOCHES ]

11:21.208 --> 11:23.375
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:23.458 --> 11:26.542
Kara: WHAT?
NO. NO, NO. NO.

11:26.625 --> 11:29.166
I SAID -- I SAID
I WANT BUTTERSCOTCH!

11:29.250 --> 11:30.834
BUTTERSCOTCH!

11:30.917 --> 11:33.458
[ Slurring ] HOW MUCH CLEARER
CAN I MAKE IT, EUGENE?

11:33.542 --> 11:37.542
THIS IS DISCRIMINATION.

11:37.625 --> 11:40.917
[ GASPS ] THIS IS 'CAUSE
MY MOM'S A LESBIAN, ISN'T IT?

11:41.000 --> 11:42.959
KARA, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

11:43.041 --> 11:45.333
DASHIEL.

11:45.417 --> 11:47.625
YOU ARE LOOKING DASHING.

11:47.709 --> 11:49.333
HAS ANYONE
EVER TOLD YOU THAT?

11:49.417 --> 11:50.875
[ Chuckling ]
GOD, I'M SO FUNNY.

11:50.959 --> 11:52.000
ARE -- ARE YOU DRUNK?

11:52.083 --> 11:54.291
HECK, YEAH, I'M DRUNK.

11:54.375 --> 11:56.041
AND WHY SHOULDN'T I BE?

11:56.125 --> 11:59.875
THE MOST RIDICULOUSLY
GOOD-LOOKING GUY ON THE PLANET

11:59.959 --> 12:01.542
CHOSE TO LOVE ME,

12:01.625 --> 12:03.667
AND HOW DO I REPAY HIM?

12:03.750 --> 12:06.083
I BONE LEO!
Shh!

12:06.166 --> 12:08.208
I KNOW THAT, AND NOW
EVERYONE ELSE DOES, TOO.

12:08.291 --> 12:09.500
Oh, my God.

12:09.583 --> 12:11.375
I APOLOGIZE, EUGENE.
[ GROANS ]

12:11.458 --> 12:15.250
UH, MRS. ADAM,
MISS FONG, I'M SORRY.

12:15.333 --> 12:17.250
CARRY ON, EVERYONE.

12:17.333 --> 12:21.333
LISTEN, YOU NEED TO WORK
ON YOUR INSIDE VOICE.

12:21.417 --> 12:23.750
I DON'T CARE WHO KNOWS IT!
NOTHING MATTERS ANYMORE!

12:23.834 --> 12:25.333
ALL RIGHT,
STOP BEATING YOURSELF UP

12:25.417 --> 12:27.000
OVER THE WHOLE LEO THING,
ALL RIGHT?

12:27.083 --> 12:29.208
YOU HAD NO WAY OF KNOWING HUNTER
WAS GONNA GET HIS LIVER.

12:29.291 --> 12:32.166
AND TECHNICALLY,
YOU DUMPED HIM BEFORE YOU LEFT.

12:32.250 --> 12:34.792
WHICH TECHNICALLY MAKES ME
THE WORST PERSON ON THE PLANET.

12:34.875 --> 12:36.375
[ SIGHS ]

12:36.458 --> 12:38.125
I DON'T DESERVE HIS HEART.

12:38.208 --> 12:41.250
LOOK, I'M SURE PEOPLE
HAVE LOVED YOU FOR LESS.

12:41.333 --> 12:47.208
NO. HIS <i>HEART</i> HEART
THAT HE DONATED...TO ME.

12:47.291 --> 12:48.709
HE MADE
A DIRECT DONATION?

12:48.792 --> 12:50.750
YEP.

12:50.834 --> 12:52.166
[ SCOFFS ]
AND YOU'RE SITTING HERE DRUNK

12:52.250 --> 12:53.750
AND EATING PUDDING?

12:53.834 --> 12:55.792
AND NACHOS.

12:55.875 --> 12:58.166
THE PUDDING
WAS TO WASH THEM DOWN.

12:58.250 --> 13:00.375
KARA,
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

13:00.458 --> 13:03.041
WHAT IF YOU END UP
HAVING TO GO INTO SURGERY?

13:03.125 --> 13:05.166
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE
THE SURGERY.

13:05.250 --> 13:10.291
I DON'T WANT HUNTER'S HEART.
I JUST WANT...HUNTER.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.083
I HAVE TO BURP.

13:15.166 --> 13:17.417
HEY, HAVE, UH,
YOU SEEN KARA?

13:17.500 --> 13:19.959
UH, NO, BUT I'M ABOUT TO START
MY ROUNDS, SO --

13:20.041 --> 13:21.792
WHOA, OHH.

13:24.041 --> 13:27.000
YOU TWO WOULD MAKE
BEAUTIFUL BABIES.

13:27.083 --> 13:30.500
IN CASE IT'S NOT OBVIOUS,
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

13:36.625 --> 13:39.709
I DO NOT
UNDERSTAND YOU, KARA.

13:39.792 --> 13:41.208
DID YOU COME PRE-WIRED
TO TORTURE THE WORLD?

13:41.291 --> 13:43.333
I'M SORRY I'M A MESS,
OKAY?

13:43.417 --> 13:45.291
BUT NOT ALL OF US
CAN BLOW OFF STEAM

13:45.375 --> 13:46.667
BY PLAYING DARTS

13:46.750 --> 13:48.417
AND BRO-HUGGING IT OUT
TO "PIANO MAN."

13:48.500 --> 13:49.917
I MEAN,
BESIDES THE FACT

13:50.000 --> 13:51.375
THAT YOU'RE A HEART PATIENT

13:51.458 --> 13:53.417
AND YOU SHOULDN'T EVER
BE DRINKING,

13:53.500 --> 13:55.625
YOU MIGHT HAVE AN ACTUAL HEART
ON ITS WAY TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

13:55.709 --> 13:57.500
I DON'T CARE.
I DON'T WANT IT.

13:57.583 --> 13:59.625
GOOD. BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT
GONNA GET IT LIKE THIS.

13:59.709 --> 14:01.625
HEY, HEY.

14:01.709 --> 14:03.959
She's worried
about Hunter.

14:06.041 --> 14:08.625
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHT. LOOK.

14:08.709 --> 14:10.834
YOU'RE GONNA FEEL MUCH BETTER
ONCE YOU GET REHYDRATED.

14:10.917 --> 14:12.625
AND WHAT IF I REFUSE
THE SURGERY?

14:12.709 --> 14:14.208
YOU CAN'T OPERATE ON ME,
CAN YOU?

14:14.291 --> 14:16.166
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT
RIGHT NOW, ALL RIGHT?

14:16.250 --> 14:18.625
YOU JUST GET SOME REST,
AND EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE FINE.

14:20.709 --> 14:23.125
[ SIGHS ] I ONCE DRANK
A HALF BOTTLE OF PEACH SCHNAPPS

14:23.208 --> 14:25.959
WHEN JANET MARINO TOLD EVERYONE
I HAD DANDRUFF.

14:26.041 --> 14:27.417
IT WASN'T TRUE,

14:27.500 --> 14:30.041
BUT I STILL GOT DRUNK
AND WASHED MY HAIR.

14:31.917 --> 14:34.125
BOOZE IS ALWAYS A GOOD IDEA
UNTIL IT'S NOT.

14:35.917 --> 14:37.417
SHE'S GONNA --
SHE'S GONNA PULL THROUGH.

14:37.500 --> 14:38.792
SHE'S -- [ SIGHS ]

14:38.875 --> 14:40.125
SHOULD I LET DR. GRACE
KNOW ABOUT THIS?

14:40.208 --> 14:43.375
NO. NO. UH...

14:45.417 --> 14:47.500
UNLESS YOU FEEL
LIKE YOU SHOULD.

14:47.583 --> 14:50.125
I DON'T WANT TO PUT YOU
IN AN UNCOMFORTABLE SITUATION.
NO.

14:50.208 --> 14:52.917
I DON'T SEE ANY REASON
TO INVOLVE ANYONE ELSE.

14:53.000 --> 14:55.000
[ SIGHS ]

15:05.250 --> 15:08.542
DUDE, KENJI TOLD ME
THE GOOD NEWS.

15:08.625 --> 15:10.959
ALL RIGHT, HOW ABOUT A LITTLE
IMPROMPTU GOING-AWAY?

15:11.041 --> 15:12.917
GOT THE WHITE WIDOW
IF YOU GOT THE TIME.

15:13.000 --> 15:15.333
IT'S PROBABLY
NOT A GOOD IDEA TO SMOKE

15:15.417 --> 15:16.750
WITH MY PARENTS
WANDERING AROUND.

15:16.834 --> 15:18.375
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHT, FINE.

15:18.458 --> 15:21.250
BUT WE GOT TO DO
SOMETHING CEREMONIAL, MAN.

15:21.333 --> 15:23.917
A RED BANDER
IS LEAVING THE FOLD TODAY.

15:24.000 --> 15:25.125
MAYBE.

15:25.208 --> 15:27.375
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

15:27.458 --> 15:28.583
WITH EVERYTHING GOING ON,

15:28.667 --> 15:30.375
IT DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT
TO TAKE OFF.

15:30.458 --> 15:32.333
DUDE, STOP WORRYING
ABOUT KARA, MAN.

15:32.417 --> 15:34.750
THEY'RE PUMPING THAT GIRL UP
WITH SO MUCH B12,

15:34.834 --> 15:36.750
SHE'LL BE ABLE TO CLIMB
MACHU PICCHU.

15:36.834 --> 15:38.375
I WAS TALKING ABOUT EMMA.

15:38.458 --> 15:40.375
YOU MEAN
THE GIRL WHO DUMPED YOU?

15:40.458 --> 15:41.709
SHE BROKE UP WITH ME.

15:41.792 --> 15:42.792
I MEAN,
IT DOESN'T MATTER ANYMORE.

15:42.875 --> 15:44.083
SHE'S FREAKING OUT.

15:44.166 --> 15:45.333
SHE BEGGED ME
NOT TO GO ANYWHERE.

15:45.417 --> 15:47.000
DOESN'T THAT
TELL YOU SOMETHING?

15:47.083 --> 15:49.625
RIGHT. IT TELLS ME SHE'S SCARED,
AND SHE NEEDS A FRIEND.

15:49.709 --> 15:51.625
[ SIGHS ]

15:51.709 --> 15:53.375
LOOK, MAN.

15:53.458 --> 15:56.291
YOU'RE MY FRIEND,
AND I LOVE YOU LIKE A BROTHER,

15:56.375 --> 15:58.417
WHICH IS WHY I GOT TO KEEP IT
REAL WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

16:00.041 --> 16:02.583
YOU MAKE HER WORSE.

16:02.667 --> 16:05.208
AS LONG AS SHE HAS YOU
TO FOCUS ON,

16:05.291 --> 16:07.625
SHE'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO FOCUS ON HERSELF.

16:08.750 --> 16:12.250
NOW, IF YOU REALLY WANT
TO HELP EMMA...

16:12.333 --> 16:13.917
YOU GOT TO SET HER FREE.

16:18.667 --> 16:20.083
MY NAME IS JORDI PALACIOS,

16:20.166 --> 16:22.542
AND ALTHOUGH I COME
FROM HUMBLE BEGINNINGS,

16:22.625 --> 16:23.875
WHEN I'M EMANCIPATED --

16:23.959 --> 16:25.959
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

16:29.834 --> 16:30.750
[ BEEP ]

16:30.834 --> 16:33.750
HELLO?

16:33.834 --> 16:36.000
YEAH, YEAH, THIS IS JORDI.

16:36.083 --> 16:39.083
WHO IS THIS?

16:39.166 --> 16:42.500
WAIT. YOU GOT MY NUMBER
FROM WHO?

16:42.583 --> 16:44.709
LOOK, I DON'T CARE
WHAT ALEXA SAID.

16:44.792 --> 16:46.208
DON'T EVER CALL ME AGAIN.

16:46.291 --> 16:48.959
[ BEEP ]

16:49.041 --> 16:51.041
[ SIGHS ]

16:53.125 --> 16:54.875
JORDI.

16:54.959 --> 16:56.417
NURSE JACKSON.
[ SIGHS ]

16:56.500 --> 16:57.834
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

16:57.917 --> 16:59.542
RESEARCHING
MY NEXT LEGAL THRILLER.

16:59.625 --> 17:01.291
SOMEBODY'S
GOT TO TAKE GRISHAM DOWN.

17:01.375 --> 17:03.333
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
I'M HERE FOR YOU.

17:03.417 --> 17:05.250
LOOKS LIKE I GOT HERE
JUST IN TIME, TOO.

17:05.333 --> 17:07.709
YOU CAN'T BE SWEATING LIKE THIS
IN FRONT OF THE JUDGE, BABY.

17:07.792 --> 17:09.542
LOOK LIKE YOU JUST ROBBED
A LIQUOR STORE.

17:09.625 --> 17:11.083
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH, I PROBABLY
SHOULDN'T HAVE TAKEN THE STAIRS.

17:11.166 --> 17:12.834
PROBABLY NOT.

17:12.917 --> 17:15.500
LOOK, LET'S GET YOU SOME WATER
BEFORE YOU HAVE TO GO IN.

17:20.333 --> 17:23.000
HEY.
HOW YOU DOING?

17:23.083 --> 17:24.917
STABLE.

17:25.000 --> 17:27.083
THE DOCTORS SAY MY SLOW HEART
RHYTHM SHOULD CORRECT ITSELF,

17:27.166 --> 17:29.667
BUT THEY WON'T KNOW
FOR A FEW DAYS, SO...

17:29.750 --> 17:31.333
LOOKS LIKE I'M BACK.

17:31.417 --> 17:33.709
SHORTEST ESCAPE EVER.

17:33.792 --> 17:35.834
WELL,
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

17:35.917 --> 17:37.917
IN THE FALL OF 1941,

17:38.000 --> 17:40.458
JOHN BAYLESS TRIED
TO ESCAPE ALCATRAZ,

17:40.542 --> 17:42.750
AND HE STEPPED ONE FOOT
IN THE WATER AND GAVE UP.

17:44.583 --> 17:47.917
SO, MY PARENTS
DROVE DOWN TODAY.

17:48.000 --> 17:49.667
REALLY?
WHERE ARE THEY?

17:49.750 --> 17:52.917
SIGNING
DISCHARGE PAPERWORK.

17:53.000 --> 17:56.166
I'M GOING HOME EARLY.

17:56.250 --> 17:59.333
OH.

17:59.417 --> 18:00.834
WELL, THAT'S GREAT.

18:00.917 --> 18:03.417
YOU WORKED REALLY HARD, LEO.
YOU DESERVE IT.

18:03.500 --> 18:06.208
THANKS.

18:06.291 --> 18:07.917
AND HOPEFULLY
I'LL BE OUT SOON, TOO,

18:08.000 --> 18:11.542
AND I CAN COME VISIT YOU
IN BAKERSFIELD.

18:11.625 --> 18:13.125
SURE.

18:13.208 --> 18:16.792
YEAH, WE'LL -- WE'LL HANG OUT
AS, UH -- AS FRIENDS.

18:18.625 --> 18:20.417
ABOUT THAT.
I MADE A MISTAKE.

18:20.500 --> 18:22.291
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE TO --
NO, LEO.

18:22.375 --> 18:24.875
I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT BREAKING UP WITH YOU.

18:24.959 --> 18:28.041
I WASN'T THINKING CLEARLY.
IT'S NOT WHAT I WANT.

18:29.166 --> 18:31.959
EMMA, YOU PASSED OUT.
YOU'RE BACK IN THE HOSPITAL.

18:32.041 --> 18:34.208
THE DOCTORS ARE SAYING THERE ARE
SERIOUS THINGS WRONG WITH YOU.

18:34.291 --> 18:35.750
THIS IS BEYOND US NOW.

18:35.834 --> 18:37.208
WELL,
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE.

18:37.291 --> 18:39.041
I CAN WORK ON MYSELF
AND STILL HAVE YOU.

18:39.125 --> 18:41.583
NO.

18:41.667 --> 18:43.500
NO, WE CAN'T.

18:43.583 --> 18:45.291
WHY NOT?

18:45.375 --> 18:47.625
BECAUSE, UH...

18:47.709 --> 18:51.375
"BECAUSE, UH" WHY?

18:51.458 --> 18:53.792
I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

18:56.208 --> 18:59.667
[ SIGHS ]
'CAUSE I SLEPT WITH KARA.

19:02.625 --> 19:03.959
GET OUT.

19:04.041 --> 19:06.917
EMMA, I'M SORRY.
GET OUT OF MY ROOM, LEO!

19:07.000 --> 19:09.583
GET OUT!

19:20.834 --> 19:23.166
Kara:
HI. IT'S ME.

19:23.250 --> 19:26.792
I GUESS WE HAVEN'T SPOKEN
SINCE THAT TURBULENCE.

19:26.875 --> 19:30.000
THANK YOU, BY THE WAY,
FOR LANDING THAT PLANE...

19:30.083 --> 19:33.333
EVEN THOUGH ST. BARTS
WAS WAY OVERRATED.

19:33.417 --> 19:35.792
ANYWAY, UM...

19:35.875 --> 19:37.542
HUNTER WOULD KILL ME
FOR DOING THIS,

19:37.625 --> 19:39.250
BUT SOMEBODY
NEEDS TO SPEAK FOR HIM

19:39.333 --> 19:44.792
BECAUSE HE'S YOUNG
AND BEAUTIFUL AND SMART,

19:44.875 --> 19:46.917
AND HE HAS SO MANY GIFTS --

19:49.542 --> 19:51.667
DON'T STOP.

19:51.750 --> 19:54.500
YOU'RE DOING A HELL OF A LOT
BETTER THAN I'VE BEEN DOING.

19:54.583 --> 19:59.834
I JUST SAID "HELL" IN A CHAPEL,
THUS PROVING MY POINT.

20:04.917 --> 20:07.000
SO, I HEARD THAT HUNTER'S
DONATING HIS HEART TO YOU.

20:07.083 --> 20:09.834
DON'T WORRY.
I'M NOT GONNA TAKE IT.

20:11.083 --> 20:12.875
WHY WOULDN'T YOU TAKE IT?

20:12.959 --> 20:14.959
BECAUSE I CAN'T.

20:15.041 --> 20:18.166
I-I DON'T DESERVE IT,
AND I DON'T WANT HUNTER TO DIE.

20:18.250 --> 20:19.166
NO, NEITHER DO I.

20:19.250 --> 20:20.917
AND JUST TO BE CLEAR,

20:21.000 --> 20:21.667
IF THERE'S A CHOICE BETWEEN
HIM DYING AND YOU DYING,

20:21.750 --> 20:23.125
I'D CHOOSE YOU.

20:23.208 --> 20:26.041
RIGHT. OBVIOUSLY.
YOU'RE HIS SISTER, SO --

20:26.125 --> 20:27.542
NO, EVEN IF I WEREN'T
HIS SISTER.

20:27.625 --> 20:29.208
I BET IF WE TOOK A POLL
AROUND HERE

20:29.291 --> 20:31.250
OF, "WHO WOULD YOU RATHER DIE,
KARA OR HUNTER?"

20:31.333 --> 20:33.500
IF WE PULLED SOME SORT
OF "AMERICAN IDOL" THING

20:33.583 --> 20:34.667
WHERE YOU COULD TEXT IN
YOUR RESULTS,

20:34.750 --> 20:36.125
YOU -- YOU'D GO DOWN
PRETTY EASY.

20:36.208 --> 20:37.166
AND THEN RYAN SEACREST
GIVES YOU THAT SAD HUG,

20:37.250 --> 20:38.875
AND OFF YOU GO.

20:38.959 --> 20:40.959
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,
I DON'T THINK RYAN'S A HUGGER.

20:41.041 --> 20:43.041
I THINK YOU'RE CONFUSING HIM
FOR HEIDI KLUM,

20:43.125 --> 20:44.500
WHO OCCASIONALLY HUGS.

20:44.583 --> 20:48.000
BUT SECOND OF ALL, I...

20:48.083 --> 20:49.709
NOTHING. NEVER MIND.

20:49.792 --> 20:50.959
WHAT? YOU DISAGREE?

20:51.041 --> 20:54.250
I DON'T,
BUT YOUR BROTHER MIGHT.

20:54.333 --> 20:56.792
TRUE. BUT YOU DON'T GIVE A CRAP
ABOUT MY BROTHER.

20:56.875 --> 20:59.125
OF COURSE I DO.

20:59.208 --> 21:01.208
THEN WHY WOULD YOU DENY HIM
HIS LAST WISH?

21:02.750 --> 21:04.291
THIS IS BIGGER
THAN YOU AND ME.

21:04.375 --> 21:08.792
SO IF HE LOVES YOU,
JUST LOVE HIM BACK.

21:12.500 --> 21:15.750
GOOD.

21:15.834 --> 21:17.625
THEN LET'S PRAY, BITCH.

21:24.834 --> 21:27.875
Judge Mejia:
SO, MR. PALACIOS,

21:27.959 --> 21:29.583
YOU APPEAR
TO HAVE YOUR DUCKS IN A ROW.

21:29.667 --> 21:31.792
I SEE TRANSCRIPTS,
BANK STATEMENTS,

21:31.875 --> 21:33.333
THIS VERY NICE LETTER

21:33.417 --> 21:35.417
FROM PROFESSOR RUBEN GARCIA
ON YOUR BEHALF.

21:35.500 --> 21:37.333
BUT WHAT I'D LIKE
TO HEAR FROM YOU

21:37.417 --> 21:40.417
IS HOW YOU SEE YOUR LIFE
AS AN ADULT.

21:45.041 --> 21:46.458
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

21:46.542 --> 21:48.667
MY NAME IS JORDI PALACIOS,

21:48.750 --> 21:50.166
AND ALTHOUGH I COME
FROM VERY HUMBLE BEGINNING--

21:50.250 --> 21:51.709
Judge Mejia: WAIT, NO.

21:51.792 --> 21:54.250
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ANY PREPARED REMARKS.

21:54.333 --> 21:55.667
PUT THEM AWAY.

21:55.750 --> 21:57.625
YOU'RE NOT THANKING
YOUR AGENT HERE.

21:57.709 --> 21:59.417
YOU'RE SPEAKING
FROM YOUR SOUL.

21:59.500 --> 22:02.667
IMAGINE FIVE YEARS FROM NOW --
YOUR CANCER IS GONE,

22:02.750 --> 22:05.250
AND YOU'RE OUT THERE
DOING YOUR THING.

22:05.333 --> 22:08.125
TELL ME ABOUT <i>THAT,</i>
JORDI PALACIOS.

22:08.208 --> 22:12.125
WHAT KIND OF ADULT
DO YOU SEE HIM BEING?

22:16.417 --> 22:18.208
FOR THE PILLS.

22:18.291 --> 22:19.583
UM...

22:24.041 --> 22:26.083
UM...

22:29.917 --> 22:32.041
I GUESS...

22:32.125 --> 22:33.500
[ HEART BEATING ]

22:33.583 --> 22:35.000
I MEAN...

22:36.500 --> 22:39.583
I'M SORRY. I DON'T FEEL
VERY WELL ALL OF A SUDDEN.

22:41.250 --> 22:42.750
JORDI.

22:45.250 --> 22:47.959
UH, EXCUSE ME, JUDGE.
IF I MAY?

22:48.041 --> 22:49.166
WHO ARE YOU?

22:49.250 --> 22:50.542
MY NAME IS DENA JACKSON.

22:50.625 --> 22:52.166
I WORK AT OCEAN PARK HOSPITAL,

22:52.250 --> 22:55.000
WHERE JORDI IS CURRENTLY
UNDERGOING CHEMOTHERAPY.

22:55.083 --> 22:57.250
[ SIGHS ]

23:01.083 --> 23:03.417
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:03.500 --> 23:07.041
I-I'VE ONLY KNOWN JORDI
A FEW WEEKS NOW.

23:07.125 --> 23:10.667
HIS STORY SHOULD BE
THE SADDEST STORY EVER,

23:10.750 --> 23:12.542
BUT YOU SPEND
FIVE MINUTES WITH HIM,

23:12.625 --> 23:14.000
AND SOMEHOW IT ISN'T

23:14.083 --> 23:15.542
BECAUSE WHILE EVERYONE ELSE
IS CRYING

23:15.625 --> 23:17.500
ABOUT ALL THE THINGS
THAT THEY DON'T HAVE,

23:17.583 --> 23:22.208
THIS KID, A SICK KID,
IS -- IS PLOTTING HIS NEXT MOVE.

23:22.291 --> 23:24.041
NOW, HE CAME TO THIS COURT TODAY

23:24.125 --> 23:27.166
ASKING TO OFFICIALLY BE NAMED
AN ADULT,

23:27.250 --> 23:29.417
BUT TRUST ME WHEN I SAY

23:29.500 --> 23:31.542
HE HAS MORE YEARS
IN THAT SOUL OF HIS

23:31.625 --> 23:35.875
THAN ALL OF US COMBINED.

23:35.959 --> 23:39.834
HE'S ALREADY A GROWN-UP,
YOUR HONOR.

23:39.917 --> 23:41.709
SO PLEASE...

23:41.792 --> 23:46.417
I JUST ASK THAT YOU GRANT HIM
THE ONE THING THE WORLD WON'T --

23:46.500 --> 23:48.291
A BREAK.

23:51.667 --> 23:53.583
MISS...
JACKSON.

23:53.667 --> 23:56.291
...JACKSON.

23:56.375 --> 24:00.083
I'M MOVED. REALLY.

24:00.166 --> 24:02.458
AND I DON'T EVEN CRY WHEN
MY GRANDKIDS COLOR ME STUFF.

24:03.875 --> 24:06.208
BUT I CAN'T,
IN GOOD CONSCIENCE,

24:06.291 --> 24:09.750
SEND A 15-YEAR-OLD
WITH CANCER

24:09.834 --> 24:12.542
OUT INTO THE WORLD
TO FEND FOR HIMSELF,

24:12.625 --> 24:14.750
NOT WHEN HE CAN'T EVEN FEND
FOR HIMSELF IN HERE.

24:16.250 --> 24:19.750
I'M SORRY,
BUT HIS EMANCIPATION IS DENIED.

24:19.834 --> 24:21.125
[ GAVEL BANGS ]

24:27.208 --> 24:29.834
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

24:29.917 --> 24:32.875
RATHER THAN PUTTING EVERYBODY
THROUGH THE MISERY OF AN APPEAL,

24:32.959 --> 24:35.750
MAYBE IT'S BETTER IF WE JUST
HONOR WHAT HUNTER WANTED.

24:35.834 --> 24:38.583
RIGHT. THANK YOU.
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

24:38.667 --> 24:41.166
SO, HOW'S SHE DOING TODAY?
KARA?

24:41.250 --> 24:42.291
SHE'S GOOD.

24:42.375 --> 24:43.583
STABLE?
NORMAL, YEAH.

24:43.667 --> 24:45.750
SOBER?

24:45.834 --> 24:46.834
WHAT?

24:46.917 --> 24:48.792
[ SCOFFS ]
I KNEW IT.

24:48.875 --> 24:50.208
YOU THINK I'M AN IDIOT,
THAT I CAN'T LOOK AT HER CHART

24:50.291 --> 24:51.667
AND SEE THAT YOU ORDERED
ENOUGH FLUIDS

24:51.750 --> 24:53.333
TO HYDRATE
A FOOTBALL TEAM?
YOU WERE --

24:53.417 --> 24:55.333
YOU WERE CHECKING UP ON ME.
NO, I WAS DOING MY JOB.

24:55.417 --> 24:58.083
THIS IS SO LIKE YOU --
ENTRAPMENT, MANIPULATION.

24:58.166 --> 25:00.125
AND YOU'LL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO WIN, RIGHT?

25:00.208 --> 25:02.834
EVEN IF IT MEANS LYING
OR GOING BEHIND MY BACK?

25:02.917 --> 25:04.792
IF YOU WEREN'T SO STUBBORN,
I WOULDN'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

25:04.875 --> 25:07.000
OH! SEE? THIS IS WHAT WAS
SO GOOD ABOUT SAM.

25:07.083 --> 25:09.834
EVEN IF HE WASN'T THE MOST
EXCITING PERSON ON THE PLANET,

25:09.917 --> 25:11.500
I ALWAYS KNEW
WHAT HE WAS THINKING.

25:11.583 --> 25:13.000
YOU SAID "WAS."
WHAT?

25:13.083 --> 25:15.500
YOU SAID,
"WAS SO GOOD ABOUT SAM."

25:15.583 --> 25:16.959
PAST TENSE.
YOU BREAK UP?

25:17.041 --> 25:19.500
ARE WE REALLY TALKING ABOUT THIS
RIGHT NOW?

25:19.583 --> 25:21.583
[ MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY ]

25:28.917 --> 25:30.458
HUNTER.

25:42.417 --> 25:44.542
YOU KNOW,
I SHOULDN'T BE IN HERE,

25:44.625 --> 25:48.041
BUT THEN AGAIN,
NEITHER SHOULD YOU.

25:48.125 --> 25:51.375
NEITHER OF US SHOULD BE,
BUT HERE WE ARE.

25:51.458 --> 25:53.750
AND THE THING IS,

25:53.834 --> 25:56.458
IS IF IT WEREN'T
FOR THIS FREAKIN' HOSPITAL,

25:56.542 --> 25:59.375
I WOULD NEVER HAVE MET YOU,
SO...

25:59.458 --> 26:02.041
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE THERE'S A REASON.

26:04.834 --> 26:07.125
MAYBE I LOVE YOU.

26:08.792 --> 26:09.875
[ SNIFFLES ]

26:09.959 --> 26:13.792
MAYBE I LOVE YOU,
HUNTER.

26:13.875 --> 26:16.709
AND...

26:16.792 --> 26:21.583
IN CASE I DO,
YOU CAN'T DIE.

26:21.667 --> 26:23.792
PLEASE.

26:25.834 --> 26:29.583
[ Voice breaking ]
PLEASE, DON'T DIE.

26:29.667 --> 26:31.667
[ SNIFFS ]

26:37.333 --> 26:39.959
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

26:43.208 --> 26:44.750
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

26:44.834 --> 26:48.500
HUNTER? HELP!
S-SOMEONE HELP!

26:48.583 --> 26:50.417
HIS ALARM'S GOING OFF!
I DON'T --

26:52.542 --> 26:54.875
HEART RATE'S DROPPING.
PAGE DR. KING!
HUNTER?

26:54.959 --> 26:58.750
HUNTER?
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

26:58.834 --> 27:00.083
HUNTER?

27:05.500 --> 27:07.875
WELL...

27:07.959 --> 27:10.125
THE GOOD NEWS IS,

27:10.208 --> 27:13.458
YOU CAN REAPPLY FOR EMANCIPATION
IN THREE MONTHS.

27:13.542 --> 27:16.834
THE BAD NEWS IS, I WILL NOT
BE THE NEXT SONIA SOTOMAYOR.

27:19.041 --> 27:20.458
I MESSED UP.

27:20.542 --> 27:22.000
DON'T BE HARD ON YOURSELF.
YOU JUST GOT NERVOUS.

27:22.083 --> 27:24.667
NO, I MEAN, I DID SOMETHING
REALLY STUPID.

27:24.750 --> 27:26.542
WHAT?

27:30.250 --> 27:31.792
I SOLD DRUGS.

27:31.875 --> 27:33.583
THAT'S HOW I GOT THE MONEY
FOR THE APPLICATION.

27:33.667 --> 27:35.208
WHAT KIND OF DRUGS?

27:35.291 --> 27:36.709
PAIN MEDS.

27:36.792 --> 27:38.625
SOME I STOLE OFF OTHER PATIENTS,
SOME WERE MINE.

27:38.709 --> 27:41.542
OH, MY GOD, JORDI.
WHY DIDN'T YOU ASK FOR HELP?

27:41.625 --> 27:43.625
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO ASK FOR HELP.

27:43.709 --> 27:44.959
I'M NOT WIRED THAT WAY.

27:45.041 --> 27:48.250
BUT THIS?
THIS WAS EASY.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.250
I DIDN'T EVEN HAVE TO
THINK ABOUT IT, REALLY.

27:50.333 --> 27:51.917
IT JUST CAME NATURALLY.

27:53.208 --> 27:54.875
AND THEN WHEN THE JUDGE
ASKED ME

27:54.959 --> 27:56.375
WHAT KIND OF PERSON I THOUGHT
I'D BE IN FIVE YEARS,

27:56.458 --> 27:57.375
I KNEW.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.834
I AM WHO I AM ALREADY.

27:59.917 --> 28:02.000
I'M HER.

28:02.083 --> 28:03.417
WHO?

28:03.500 --> 28:05.250
MY MOTHER.

28:06.917 --> 28:09.125
TELL ME SOMETHING.

28:09.208 --> 28:10.458
IF YOUR MOTHER HAD DONE
WHAT YOU DID,

28:10.542 --> 28:11.917
WOULD SHE HAVE
COME CLEAN?

28:12.000 --> 28:14.000
I MEAN, YOU GOT AWAY WITH IT,
DIDN'T YOU?

28:14.083 --> 28:16.041
YOU WERE HOME FREE.

28:16.125 --> 28:17.875
BUT INSTEAD OF CASHING IN
YOUR CHIPS,

28:17.959 --> 28:19.500
YOU WALKED
AWAY FROM THE TABLE.

28:19.583 --> 28:21.208
AND YOU TOLD THE TRUTH.

28:22.625 --> 28:27.166
LISTEN, JORDI, WE ALL INHERIT
THINGS FROM OUR PARENTS.

28:27.250 --> 28:28.709
BUT IT'S UP TO US

28:28.792 --> 28:31.083
TO KEEP THE GOOD STUFF
AND THROW THE REST AWAY.

28:31.166 --> 28:34.500
THAT'S WHAT YOU DID TODAY.
THAT'S WHY I'M PROUD OF YOU.

28:34.583 --> 28:36.000
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:36.083 --> 28:38.750
ACCORDING TO MY ABUELA,
I DID GET MY DAD'S HAIR.

28:38.834 --> 28:40.291
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

28:40.375 --> 28:41.959
I INHERITED MY MOTHER'S
SUNNY DISPOSITION.

28:42.041 --> 28:44.041
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

28:49.792 --> 28:51.291
MR. CHOTA.

28:53.166 --> 28:55.375
THIS YOUR CLASSROOM?

28:55.458 --> 28:57.083
YEAH.

28:57.166 --> 28:59.458
YEAH, I MEAN,
IT'S NOT A REAL CLASSROOM,

28:59.542 --> 29:02.250
BUT THEY TRY.

29:02.333 --> 29:05.291
EMMA'S ALWAYS BEEN GOOD
ABOUT HER SCHOOLWORK.

29:05.375 --> 29:08.041
I DON'T THINK
SHE'S MISSED AN ASSIGNMENT

29:08.125 --> 29:09.583
SINCE SHE'S BEEN HERE.

29:09.667 --> 29:12.750
THAT'S EMMA.

29:12.834 --> 29:15.792
SO, YOU -- YOU KNOW HER?

29:15.875 --> 29:18.709
I THOUGHT I DID.

29:18.792 --> 29:21.083
I THOUGHT I MIGHT HAVE
EVEN BEEN HELPING HER.

29:21.166 --> 29:24.625
BUT CAN I BE HONEST
WITH YOU?

29:24.709 --> 29:26.166
PLEASE.

29:26.250 --> 29:30.792
WE LIVE
IN THIS WEIRD WORLD HERE.

29:30.875 --> 29:32.917
AND IT'S NOT
JUST THAT EVERYONE'S SICK.

29:33.000 --> 29:35.583
IT'S THAT WE'RE ALL ALONE.

29:35.667 --> 29:39.417
AND THERE ARE DOCTORS
AND NURSES,

29:39.500 --> 29:44.083
BUT MOSTLY,
WE'RE BY OURSELVES.

29:44.166 --> 29:47.333
AND IN SOME WAYS, IT FEELS
LIKE WE'RE ALL GROWN UP.

29:49.041 --> 29:50.417
BUT WE'RE NOT.

29:50.500 --> 29:52.834
NOT REALLY.

29:52.917 --> 29:58.125
WE STILL NEED OUR PARENTS.
SHE NEEDS YOU.

29:58.208 --> 30:00.500
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO FIX HER.

30:00.583 --> 30:05.875
YOU DON'T HAVE TO FIX HER.
YOU JUST HAVE TO BE HERE.

30:10.083 --> 30:11.542
[ SIGHS ]

30:25.625 --> 30:29.291
EMMA?
I THOUGHT YOU WENT HOME.

30:29.375 --> 30:30.875
COULDN'T STAY AWAY.

30:33.083 --> 30:36.000
UM, CAN I COME IN?

30:36.083 --> 30:38.333
YEAH.

30:38.417 --> 30:42.000
SO, HUNTER JUST HAD
ANOTHER SURGERY,

30:42.083 --> 30:44.875
AND HE GOT A LIVER,
BUT HE WAS IN ICU --

30:44.959 --> 30:46.834
I KNOW YOU SLEPT WITH LEO.

30:49.041 --> 30:50.750
OH.

30:50.834 --> 30:53.792
YEAH.

30:53.875 --> 30:56.208
YOU DON'T SEEM SHOCKED.

30:56.291 --> 30:58.500
I'M NOT.

30:58.583 --> 31:00.834
RIGHT.

31:00.917 --> 31:03.375
I GUESS I WOULDN'T BE,
EITHER.

31:03.458 --> 31:05.792
NOT -- NOT BECAUSE
OF LEO AND I, OBVIOUSLY.

31:05.875 --> 31:08.250
I MEAN, THERE'S NOTHING
GOING ON BETWEEN US.

31:08.333 --> 31:10.583
IT HAPPENED
FOR ALL OF THE WRONG REASONS.

31:10.667 --> 31:12.375
STUPID REASONS.

31:12.458 --> 31:14.333
BUT THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

31:14.417 --> 31:16.500
NO. IT'S NOT.

31:16.583 --> 31:20.250
THE POINT IS, YOU WOULD NEVER
DO SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

31:20.333 --> 31:22.542
NOT IN A MILLION YEARS.

31:22.625 --> 31:25.375
RIGHT.

31:25.458 --> 31:27.041
AND I WOULD.

31:27.125 --> 31:28.917
AND THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE NOT SHOCKED.

31:29.000 --> 31:32.709
YOU KNOW, AT THE END OF THE DAY,
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON.

31:32.792 --> 31:34.542
YOU WOULD NEVER HURT A SOUL.

31:34.625 --> 31:37.125
IN FACT, THE ONLY PERSON
YOU'VE EVER HURT IS YOURSELF.

31:37.208 --> 31:40.083
WHEREAS I --

31:40.166 --> 31:43.667
I HURT EVERYONE
ALL THE TIME.

31:45.709 --> 31:47.125
I'M SORRY.

31:49.792 --> 31:53.709
I MAY HAVE SCREWED UP
MY HEART.

31:53.792 --> 31:56.709
THE DOCTOR SAID...

31:56.792 --> 31:59.417
I DON'T KNOW, BUT THE POINT IS,
I MIGHT ACTUALLY BE SICK NOW.

31:59.500 --> 32:03.417
EMMA...
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN SICK.

32:03.500 --> 32:09.750
I KNOW, BUT I'VE NEVER FELT LIKE
I'VE LOST CONTROL LIKE THIS.

32:09.834 --> 32:12.166
THIS WHOLE TIME,

32:12.250 --> 32:14.583
I KEPT THINKING
THAT I WAS THE ONE IN CHARGE,

32:14.667 --> 32:16.625
BUT I WASN'T.

32:19.000 --> 32:22.375
SO THE FACT
THAT YOU SLEPT WITH LEO --

32:22.458 --> 32:27.166
DON'T GET ME WRONG. I HATE IT.
I HATE EVERYTHING ABOUT IT.

32:27.250 --> 32:31.583
BUT RIGHT NOW, I JUST --

32:31.667 --> 32:34.125
I DON'T WANT TO BE ALONE.

32:35.458 --> 32:37.667
NEITHER DO I.

32:39.834 --> 32:43.458
BE REALLY NICE IF WE COULD
BE FRIENDS, EVEN JUST FOR NOW.

32:43.542 --> 32:44.834
YEAH.

32:44.917 --> 32:47.417
I WAS THINKING
THE SAME THING.

32:47.500 --> 32:52.959
YOU KNOW, IT WOULD HELP IF WE
HAD ANYTHING IN COMMON, BUT...

32:53.041 --> 32:56.041
OH! I JUST FOUND OUT
I HATE MY MOM.

32:56.125 --> 32:58.208
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:58.291 --> 33:00.083
OKAY.
I CAN WORK WITH THAT.

33:00.166 --> 33:02.375
[ LAUGHS ]

33:02.458 --> 33:03.667
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

33:03.750 --> 33:05.458
HEART RATE'S 162.

33:05.542 --> 33:07.542
Dr. King:
ANOTHER UNIT OF FFP.

33:07.625 --> 33:08.792
Dr. McAndrew:
I CAN'T SEE THE BLEEDER.

33:08.875 --> 33:10.291
Dr. Grace: MORE SUCTION.

33:10.375 --> 33:12.041
THERE IT IS. GOT IT.

33:12.125 --> 33:14.083
LOOKS LIKE A HALF-CENTIMETER
RUPTURE RIGHT BY THE LEFT --

33:14.166 --> 33:15.625
LEFT HEPATIC VEIN.

33:15.709 --> 33:17.291
FORCEPS.

33:17.375 --> 33:18.834
UM, CLAMP, PLEASE.

33:18.917 --> 33:20.375
SUTURES.

33:20.458 --> 33:23.166
SUCTION OVER THERE.
SUCTION OVER THERE.

33:25.125 --> 33:26.709
WE'RE LOSING
THE ALINE TRACE.

33:26.792 --> 33:29.166
Dr. King: HANG ANOTHER
BAG OF BLOOD RIGHT NOW.

33:29.250 --> 33:31.208
RUPTURE'S MUCH BIGGER
THAN I THOUGHT. CLAMP.

33:31.291 --> 33:32.250
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

33:32.333 --> 33:34.834
WE'RE LOSING HIM.

33:34.917 --> 33:36.333
I LOST IT.
I CAN'T SEE THE BLEEDER.

33:36.417 --> 33:37.709
THERE'S TOO MUCH BLOOD.

33:37.792 --> 33:41.458
[ FLATLINE ]
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.

33:43.500 --> 33:45.667
HE'S GONE.

33:45.750 --> 33:48.375
LAP PAD. LAP PAD.
I NEED A LAP PAD.

33:48.458 --> 33:49.667
CLAMP.

33:49.750 --> 33:51.208
I NEED SOMEONE
TO CLEAR THE FIELD.

33:51.291 --> 33:53.333
I NEED SOMEONE
TO CLEAR THIS FIELD!

33:53.417 --> 33:54.834
ADAM.

33:54.917 --> 33:57.250
COME ON!
I NEED HELP HERE!
ADAM.

34:25.000 --> 34:26.333
WHAT IS IT, BRITTANY?

34:26.417 --> 34:28.792
I NEED YOU TO COME
DOWN TO MRI RIGHT NOW.

34:31.208 --> 34:33.875
I-I HAVE TO GO.
GO.

34:36.792 --> 34:39.959
TIME OF DEATH -- 5:22 P.M.

34:48.291 --> 34:51.250
Dr. Grace: THE BLOOD LOSS
WAS ULTIMATELY TOO MUCH.

34:51.333 --> 34:53.417
[ WOMAN SOBS ]
WE DID
EVERYTHING WE COULD.

34:53.500 --> 34:56.291
AS YOU KNOW,
HUNTER WAS AN ORGAN DONOR,

34:56.375 --> 34:58.542
AND THE PREP TEAM FROM LifeShare
IS ON THEIR WAY.

34:58.625 --> 35:00.500
THEY'LL HAVE TO MOVE
QUICKLY,

35:00.583 --> 35:02.125
SO IF YOU'D LIKE TO SEE HIM,
I CAN BRING YOU.

35:02.208 --> 35:03.583
I'D LIKE TO SEE HIM,
PLEASE.

35:03.667 --> 35:04.959
OF COURSE.
PLEASE.

35:07.041 --> 35:08.750
David: NO.
NO, NO. I'M NOT GOING.

35:08.834 --> 35:10.125
NO, NO, NO!

35:10.208 --> 35:11.458
ASHLEY.

35:11.542 --> 35:13.083
I WANT HUNTER!

35:13.166 --> 35:14.709
ASHLEY, I GOT YOU.
I GOT YOU.

35:14.792 --> 35:16.667
[ SOBBING ]
IT'S OKAY.
GO TO YOUR SON.

35:16.750 --> 35:18.417
I'LL STAY WITH ASHLEY.

35:18.500 --> 35:21.083
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

35:21.166 --> 35:23.417
I GOT YOU.

35:25.000 --> 35:27.083
IT'S OKAY.

35:36.041 --> 35:38.542
HEY.

35:38.625 --> 35:40.583
THOUGHT YOU LEFT.

35:40.667 --> 35:44.250
NO, I WAS JUST, UM --
I WAS JUST WALKING THE HALLS,

35:44.333 --> 35:46.583
TRYING TO THINK
OF WHAT I COULD SAY TO YOU,

35:46.667 --> 35:48.000
HOW I CAN
MAKE THIS BETTER.

35:48.083 --> 35:49.792
WHAT'D YOU COME UP WITH?

35:49.875 --> 35:52.041
NOTHING.

35:54.000 --> 35:55.792
I'M SORRY, EMMA.

35:55.875 --> 35:57.625
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

36:01.125 --> 36:03.458
[ SNIFFS ]

36:03.542 --> 36:06.375
[ SIGHS ]

36:06.458 --> 36:08.291
WHEN YOU WERE BORN,

36:08.375 --> 36:10.250
I THOUGHT FOR SURE
YOU WERE GONNA BE A BOY.

36:10.333 --> 36:14.208
I WAS READY FOR A BOY.
PLANNING FOR A BOY.

36:14.291 --> 36:16.750
AND THEN IT WAS YOU.

36:16.834 --> 36:21.709
AND I WAS SO SCARED.

36:21.792 --> 36:23.750
I DIDN'T KNOW THE FIRST THING
ABOUT LITTLE GIRLS.

36:25.959 --> 36:27.834
BUT YOU MADE IT SO EASY
FOR ME.

36:27.917 --> 36:31.375
YOU WERE ALWAYS SO GOOD.

36:31.458 --> 36:36.166
I WISH YOU HAD COME TO ME
WHEN ALL THIS STARTED.

36:36.250 --> 36:38.208
I'M SORRY.

36:38.291 --> 36:40.834
NO, THIS IS ON ME.

36:40.917 --> 36:42.333
[ SIGHS ]

36:42.417 --> 36:44.166
I'M GONNA DO BETTER
FROM NOW ON.

36:44.250 --> 36:46.333
I PROMISE.

36:46.417 --> 36:49.458
WE'RE GONNA BEAT THIS
TOGETHER.

36:49.542 --> 36:51.125
YOU UNDERSTAND?

36:58.250 --> 36:59.750
HEY. HOW'D IT GO?

36:59.834 --> 37:01.583
IT DIDN'T.

37:01.667 --> 37:03.083
OH.
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

37:03.166 --> 37:04.542
WELL,
YOU HAVE A VISITOR.

37:04.625 --> 37:06.083
TELL HER TO GO HOME.

37:06.166 --> 37:08.542
OH, WELL, I DON'T THINK
I CAN TELL HER THAT.

37:08.625 --> 37:10.625
BUT IF YOU WANT...

37:17.458 --> 37:19.542
CAN I SPEAK TO YOU
FOR A MOMENT?

37:19.625 --> 37:20.792
YEAH.

37:20.875 --> 37:22.417
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:22.500 --> 37:23.917
ABUELA?

37:25.875 --> 37:27.750
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

37:29.625 --> 37:32.041
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:32.125 --> 37:33.709
SOMEONE CALLED ME

37:33.792 --> 37:36.792
AND THEY TOLD ME MY GRANDSON
WAS BECOMING A MAN TODAY.

37:38.041 --> 37:40.458
I THOUGHT A GIFT
WAS IN ORDER.

37:40.542 --> 37:42.583
THE JUDGE SAID NO.

37:42.667 --> 37:45.709
GOOD.
YOU'RE NOT READY.

37:45.792 --> 37:46.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:47.000 --> 37:48.500
GIVE ME A HUG, MIJITO.

37:49.917 --> 37:52.750
I RODE A BUS FOR YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:54.583 --> 37:57.375
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:57.458 --> 37:59.709
HEY.
SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.

37:59.792 --> 38:01.125
I JUST HEARD ABOUT HUNTER.

38:01.208 --> 38:02.542
